<subSubSection id="C3356FE2012A5371FF56F89AC386FA74" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B903C69012A5371FF56F89AC386FA74" blockId="3.[156,767,1695,2077]" lastBlockId="3.[821,1432,1337,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FF56F89AC62FF89E" bold="true" box="[181,293,1825,1849]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="549482CB012A5371FECEF89AC681F89E" box="[301,395,1825,1849]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity id="4CD7918C012A5371FE70F89AC6D2F89F" box="[403,472,1825,1849]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
long for 50 chaetigers, body colorless after preservation. Lateral antennae one and a half as long as the prostomium; median antenna a quarter as long as lateral ones; palps bi-articulated, as long as antennae (
<figureCitation id="131420EC012A5371FF40F818C7F8F81C" box="[163,242,1955,1979]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[156,187,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[187,1400,205,1084]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Oxydromus brevipodius sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Pol H-692). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, anterior view of right parapodium 21 (with dorsal cirrus of short type). C, anterior view of right parapodium 22 (with dorsal cirrus of long type). D, posterior view of right parapodium 21. E, enlarged anterior view of notopodium of the same. F, notochaeta. G–I, supra-acicular neurochaetae: G, inferior; H, median; I, superior. J–L, sub-acicular neurochaetae: J, superior; K, median; L, inferior. Scale bars: 1mm for A; 0.5mm for B, C; 0.2mm for D; 0.1mm for E; 0.02mm for F; 0.05mm for G–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738405/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); eyes circular, pale brown, anterior eyes larger than posterior ones. Parapodia sub-biramous (
<figureCitation id="131420EC012A5371FDA8F87FC5C9F87B" box="[587,707,1988,2012]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[156,187,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[187,1400,205,1084]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Oxydromus brevipodius sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Pol H-692). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, anterior view of right parapodium 21 (with dorsal cirrus of short type). C, anterior view of right parapodium 22 (with dorsal cirrus of long type). D, posterior view of right parapodium 21. E, enlarged anterior view of notopodium of the same. F, notochaeta. G–I, supra-acicular neurochaetae: G, inferior; H, median; I, superior. J–L, sub-acicular neurochaetae: J, superior; K, median; L, inferior. Scale bars: 1mm for A; 0.5mm for B, C; 0.2mm for D; 0.1mm for E; 0.02mm for F; 0.05mm for G–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738405/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2 B–D</figureCitation>
). Notopodial cirrophores with remarkable constriction at their middle and cylindrical distal part (
<figureCitation id="131420EC012A5371FE1DF7BEC543F7BA" box="[510,585,2053,2077]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[156,187,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[187,1400,205,1084]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Oxydromus brevipodius sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Pol H-692). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, anterior view of right parapodium 21 (with dorsal cirrus of short type). C, anterior view of right parapodium 22 (with dorsal cirrus of long type). D, posterior view of right parapodium 21. E, enlarged anterior view of notopodium of the same. F, notochaeta. G–I, supra-acicular neurochaetae: G, inferior; H, median; I, superior. J–L, sub-acicular neurochaetae: J, superior; K, median; L, inferior. Scale bars: 1mm for A; 0.5mm for B, C; 0.2mm for D; 0.1mm for E; 0.02mm for F; 0.05mm for G–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738405/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
); cirrostyles more distinctly articulated in their distal half (
<figureCitation id="131420EC012A5371FB3FFA82C246FAF6" box="[1244,1356,1337,1361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[156,187,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[187,1400,205,1084]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Oxydromus brevipodius sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Pol H-692). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, anterior view of right parapodium 21 (with dorsal cirrus of short type). C, anterior view of right parapodium 22 (with dorsal cirrus of long type). D, posterior view of right parapodium 21. E, enlarged anterior view of notopodium of the same. F, notochaeta. G–I, supra-acicular neurochaetae: G, inferior; H, median; I, superior. J–L, sub-acicular neurochaetae: J, superior; K, median; L, inferior. Scale bars: 1mm for A; 0.5mm for B, C; 0.2mm for D; 0.1mm for E; 0.02mm for F; 0.05mm for G–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738405/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2C, D</figureCitation>
); small fascicle of 3–4 forked notochaetae, with subdistal tine less than half as long as distal one (
<figureCitation id="131420EC012A5371FB98FAC1C3CDFA35" box="[1147,1223,1402,1426]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[156,187,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[187,1400,205,1084]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Oxydromus brevipodius sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Pol H-692). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, anterior view of right parapodium 21 (with dorsal cirrus of short type). C, anterior view of right parapodium 22 (with dorsal cirrus of long type). D, posterior view of right parapodium 21. E, enlarged anterior view of notopodium of the same. F, notochaeta. G–I, supra-acicular neurochaetae: G, inferior; H, median; I, superior. J–L, sub-acicular neurochaetae: J, superior; K, median; L, inferior. Scale bars: 1mm for A; 0.5mm for B, C; 0.2mm for D; 0.1mm for E; 0.02mm for F; 0.05mm for G–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738405/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
). Neuropodial lobes short and very stout (
<figureCitation id="131420EC012A5371FBEFFA21C351FA14" box="[1036,1115,1434,1459]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[156,187,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[187,1400,205,1084]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Oxydromus brevipodius sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Pol H-692). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, anterior view of right parapodium 21 (with dorsal cirrus of short type). C, anterior view of right parapodium 22 (with dorsal cirrus of long type). D, posterior view of right parapodium 21. E, enlarged anterior view of notopodium of the same. F, notochaeta. G–I, supra-acicular neurochaetae: G, inferior; H, median; I, superior. J–L, sub-acicular neurochaetae: J, superior; K, median; L, inferior. Scale bars: 1mm for A; 0.5mm for B, C; 0.2mm for D; 0.1mm for E; 0.02mm for F; 0.05mm for G–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738405/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
); compound chaetae with long, finely serrated blades (
<figureCitation id="131420EC012A5371FBF5FA00C38BFA74" box="[1046,1153,1467,1491]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[156,187,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[187,1400,205,1084]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Oxydromus brevipodius sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Pol H-692). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, anterior view of right parapodium 21 (with dorsal cirrus of short type). C, anterior view of right parapodium 22 (with dorsal cirrus of long type). D, posterior view of right parapodium 21. E, enlarged anterior view of notopodium of the same. F, notochaeta. G–I, supra-acicular neurochaetae: G, inferior; H, median; I, superior. J–L, sub-acicular neurochaetae: J, superior; K, median; L, inferior. Scale bars: 1mm for A; 0.5mm for B, C; 0.2mm for D; 0.1mm for E; 0.02mm for F; 0.05mm for G–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738405/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2G–L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3356FE2012A5371FCADFA67C4B6F992" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B903C69012A5371FCADFA67C4B6F992" blockId="3.[821,1432,1337,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FCADFA67C4CFFA53" bold="true" box="[846,965,1500,1524]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the distinctly short size of neuropodial lobes compared with other cogeneric species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3356FE2012A5376FCADF986C54BFA74" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B903C69012A5376FCADF986C54BFA74" blockId="3.[821,1432,1337,2077]" lastBlockId="4.[156,767,1402,1491]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FCADF986C4B8F9F2" bold="true" box="[846,946,1597,1621]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Remarks.</emphasis>
The detailed description of the 
<typeStatus id="549482CB012A5371FAEDF986C26DF9F2" box="[1294,1383,1597,1621]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">holotype</typeStatus>
was presented in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012A5371FC5AF9E5C347F9D1" author="Uchida, H." box="[953,1101,1630,1654]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="27 - 92" refId="ref21488" refString="Uchida, H. 2004. Hesionidae (Annelida, Polichaeta [sic]) from Japan. I. Kuroshio Biosphere 1: 27 - 92." type="journal article" year="2004">Uchida (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012A5371FBBBF9E5C24FF9D1" authority="Hiro &amp; Uchida &amp; Lopéz &amp; Sato, 2019" authorityName="Hiro &amp; Uchida &amp; Lopéz &amp; Sato" authorityYear="2019" box="[1112,1349,1630,1654]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevipodius" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FBBBF9E5C24FF9D1" box="[1112,1349,1630,1654]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Oxydromus brevipodius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2685D00012A5371FAA8F9E5C292F9D2" box="[1355,1432,1630,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012A5371FC50F9C4C3DFF931" authority="(Claparede 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Claparede" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[947,1237,1662,1686]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FC50F9C4C314F931" box="[947,1054,1662,1686]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">O. pallidus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012A5371FBC8F9C5C3C4F931" author="Claparede, E." box="[1067,1230,1662,1686]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="463 - 600" refId="ref19956" refString="Claparede, E. 1864. Glanures zootomiques parmi les Annelides de Port- Vendres (Pyrenees Orientales). Memoires de la Societe de Physique et d'Histoire Naturelles de Geneve 17: 463 - 600." type="journal article" year="1864">Claparède 1864</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, from the Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012A5371FC55F924C353F910" author="Claparede, E." box="[950,1113,1695,1719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="463 - 600" refId="ref19956" refString="Claparede, E. 1864. Glanures zootomiques parmi les Annelides de Port- Vendres (Pyrenees Orientales). Memoires de la Societe de Physique et d'Histoire Naturelles de Geneve 17: 463 - 600." type="journal article" year="1864">Claparède 1864</bibRefCitation>
) and common in western Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012A5371FC97F904C348F970" author="Parapar, J. &amp; Besteiro, C. &amp; Moreira, J." box="[884,1090,1727,1751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="210 - 267" refId="ref21036" refString="Parapar, J., Besteiro, C., and Moreira, J. 2004. Familia Hesionidae Grube, 1850. Pp. 210 - 267. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds) Annelida, Polychaeta I. Fauna Iberica, Vol. 25. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales / CSIC, Madrid." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Parapar 
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FC2CF97BC30EF970" box="[975,1028,1727,1751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
), and to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012A5371FB44F97BC47AF95F" authority="(Hoagland 1919)" baseAuthorityName="Hoagland" baseAuthorityYear="1919" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="guanicus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FB44F97BC22BF970" box="[1191,1313,1728,1751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">O. guanicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012A5371FAD1F904C463F95F" author="Hoagland, R. A." pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="571 - 591" refId="ref20581" refString="Hoagland, R. A. 1919. Polychaetous annelids from Porto Rico, the Florida Keys and Bermuda. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 41: 571 - 591." type="journal article" year="1919">Hoagland 1919</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, from the Caribbean Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012A5371FB9BF95BC212F95F" author="Hoagland, R. A." box="[1144,1304,1760,1784]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="571 - 591" refId="ref20581" refString="Hoagland, R. A. 1919. Polychaetous annelids from Porto Rico, the Florida Keys and Bermuda. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 41: 571 - 591." type="journal article" year="1919">Hoagland 1919</bibRefCitation>
), in possessing short, sub-biramous parapodia. However, the new species clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012A5371FBCEF89AC390F89E" baseAuthorityName="Claparede" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[1069,1178,1825,1849]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FBCEF89AC390F89E" box="[1069,1178,1825,1849]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">O. pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in (1) distal articulation of palps, in contrast to proximal one in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012A5371FB25F8F9C238F8FE" baseAuthorityName="Claparede" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[1222,1330,1857,1881]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FB25F8F9C238F8FE" box="[1222,1330,1857,1881]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">O. pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (2) palps as long as the lateral antennae, in contrast to those shorter than lateral antennae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012A5371FBD3F838C397F83D" baseAuthorityName="Claparede" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[1072,1181,1922,1946]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FBD3F838C397F83D" box="[1072,1181,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">O. pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and (3) larger eyes (especially in the posterior pair) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012A5371FB78F818C26AF81C" author="Parapar, J. &amp; Besteiro, C. &amp; Moreira, J." box="[1179,1376,1955,1979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="210 - 267" refId="ref21036" refString="Parapar, J., Besteiro, C., and Moreira, J. 2004. Familia Hesionidae Grube, 1850. Pp. 210 - 267. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds) Annelida, Polychaeta I. Fauna Iberica, Vol. 25. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales / CSIC, Madrid." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Parapar 
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FB12F81FC22EF81C" box="[1265,1316,1955,1979]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
). The new species differs in turn from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012A5371FB62F87FC3FDF87C" baseAuthorityName="Hoagland" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[1153,1271,1988,2011]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="guanicus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FB62F87FC3FDF87C" box="[1153,1271,1988,2011]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">O. guanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in (1) the presence of notochaetae, in contrast to the lack of the same in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012A5371FA63F85FC3EFF7BA" authority="(Rizzo and Salazar-Vallejo 2014)" baseAuthorityName="Rizzo and Salazar-Vallejo" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="guanicus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012A5371FA63F85FC487F7BB" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">O. guanicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012A5371FC78F7BFC3D7F7BA" author="Rizzo, A. E. &amp; Salazar-Vallejo, S. I." box="[923,1245,2052,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="267 - 291" refId="ref21201" refString="Rizzo, A. E. and Salazar-Vallejo, S. I. 2014. Hesionidae Grube, 1850 (Annelida: Polychaeta) from South-Southeastern Brazil, with descriptions of four new species. Zootaxa 3856: 267 - 291." type="journal article" year="2014">Rizzo and Salazar-Vallejo 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; (2) the constriction proximally situated in notopodial cirrophores, in contrast to that distally situated in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA012D5376FE07FA20C556FA15" baseAuthorityName="Rizzo and Salazar-Vallejo" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[484,604,1435,1458]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Oxydromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="guanicus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B012D5376FE07FA20C556FA15" box="[484,604,1435,1458]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">O. guanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and (3) longer lateral antennae and palps (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198012D5376FE53FA00C53CFA74" author="Uchida, H." box="[432,566,1467,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="27 - 92" refId="ref21488" refString="Uchida, H. 2004. Hesionidae (Annelida, Polichaeta [sic]) from Japan. I. Kuroshio Biosphere 1: 27 - 92." type="journal article" year="2004">Uchida 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
